**Substep: A Generative Sound Sequencer**
       Michael Mara

The project can be [downloaded from github](https://github.com/Mx7f/substep).

Build Prerequisites:
+ The [G3D Innovation Engine](https://g3d.codeplex.com/SourceControl/latest#G3D10/readme.md). This project was developed with the development version of G3D available from svn://graphics-svn.cs.williams.edu/g3d; revision 306. Foll

Build Instructions:
+ On OS X, open the terminal, change directory to substep/code, and run icompile --opt --run (icompile will have installed as part of your G3D installation).
+ On Windows, use the provided Visual Studio 2015 solution.


Use Instructions:
Instructions appear on screen, 'h' to toggle display of information
Click near corners to place playheads. Space plays/pauses time.


